Fields of Armour

War Documentary hosted by Lary Lewman, published by Discovery Channel in 1993 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

The history of armoured warfare is a history of tactics, technology and human genius. Relive the great tank battles of the twentieth century with Fields of Armour. With access to personal diaries, letters and the oral history of the men who fought these battles, Fields of Armour turns maps and tactics into fears and faces.

Series Producers : Kurt Sayenga and Steven Hoggard

4)  Hammer into Anvil 
The battle of Kursk was the turning point in World War II and saw the largest clash of tanks ever seen.

